subSubSection.paragraph:
Toes free with cutaneous edge and rudimentary interdigital basal membrane; two metatarsal tubercles (
Fig. 11
); relative length of toes: 4 > 5 = 3 > 2 > 1 . Lumbar glands large, oval, one and a half times the size of eye diameter. Vocal sacs single, median and subgular. In life, dorsally brownish with large almost symmetrical dark spots. Dark transverse bands on upper surface of arms and legs. Yellow lumbar glands with a black central ocellus covering 60 % of the gland. Brilliant red-orange spots on the groin and around lumbar glands. Dark palms and soles, with whitish palmar tubercles. Dark vocal sac, with the rest of ventral body surface being whitish and mild dotted dark. Iris gold with black reticulations.

